prompt_template:
Create a {ASPECT_RATIO} raster poster image in the Jagged Red Street Photo Event Poster Style.

Subject: {SUBJECT}
Action: {SUBJECT_ACTION}
Prop/Product: {PRODUCT_OR_PROP}
Location: {LOCATION}
Background: {BACKGROUND_ELEMENTS}
Main text: {MAIN_TEXT}
Secondary text: {SECONDARY_TEXT}
Accent symbol: {ACCENT_SYMBOL}
Wardrobe/styling: {WARDROBE_STYLE}
Style fidelity anchors: {STYLE_FIDELITY_ANCHORS}
Source content to avoid: {SOURCE_CONTENT_TO_AVOID}

Apply these fixed style rules: build the poster on a clean white field; use a central high-contrast black-and-white documentary photo block with real street-level or venue-level perspective; place enormous jagged red hand-cut display lettering across the top as the dominant graphic mass; surround red letters with thick white cut-paper gutters where they overlap the photo; add blocky black secondary lettering in the lower area; form the bottom event information from oversized uneven red and black word blocks; keep the palette strictly red, black, white, and grayscale; include only a tiny fictional badge or accent mark if needed; make the whole design feel like a raw screenprinted local event flyer with crisp pasted layers, slight handmade misalignment, hard daylight contrast, and controlled print grain.

Avoid skateboarding, skate contests, skateboard props, crouching filmers, the source poster's exact street scene, any original text, real logos, watermarks, QR codes, platform UI, polished corporate design, 3D render, vector-only flatness, comic illustration, full-color photography, gradients, beige vintage paper, neon chrome, warped unreadable text, and uncontrolled digital noise. Important content rule: match the visual style first, then change the source content completely while preserving the style fidelity anchors.
